de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.database.relation

Class MaterializedDoubleRelation

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.result.AbstractHierarchicalResult
      • de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.database.relation.AbstractRelation<Double>
        • de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.database.relation.MaterializedDoubleRelation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DatabaseQuery, DoubleRelation, ModifiableRelation<Double>, Relation<Double>, HierarchicalResult, Result

    public class MaterializedDoubleRelation
extends AbstractRelation<Double>
implements DoubleRelation
    Represents a single representation. This is attached to a DBIDs object, which you are supposed to manage first. I.e. put the new DBID in, then invoke set(), remove the DBID, then delete().
    Author:
    Erich Schubert
